> in a similar situation but much much further away from home and in the
mountains.  I ran a wire from the throttle linkage in the engine compartment
thru a opening into the body and to the front, hand throttle by pulling on
wire...... got home with very little delay.
>

I had a Corvair and the linkage connecting the throttle cable and the carbs
broke (failed weld).  I attached a string to the linkage, and then up through
the vents on the rear deck, and into the passenger compartment.  Fortunately
it was a convertible.  I think I drove like this for a few days, until the
"proper fix" using a hose clamp was employed.

